The Cross River State Police Command has read the riot act to people planning to cause trouble at the People Democratic Party (PDP) stakeholders meeting to stay away from the venue of the meeting on Sunday. The Command Public Relations Officer, DSP Irene Ugbo, stated, “This message is to warn unequivocally that person(s) or groups not on the invitation list are not permitted to loiter or gather around the venue. “Cross River State Police Command will deal decisively with anybody who ventures around this venue with intent to cause breach of Peace. “All are warned to keep the peace we are enjoying in this State for our common good” she stated, adding, “If you see something, say something” Imo prison attack: Resign now that you are in trouble – Biafra group tells Gov Uzodinma 